  "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nDevUI - config editor doesn't notify user when something goes wrong\r\n\r\nWhen the value gets updated there is \"Configuration update successful\" window in the top right corner.\r\n\r\nBut when things do not get updated, the is no notification to the end used\r\nOne needs to open console of web browser to see something like 403 Forbidden.\r\n\r\nUsers need to be informed when their config changes do not get updated.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nUsers are informed when their config changes through DevUI config editor do not get updated.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nOne needs to open console of web browser to see something like 403 Forbidden.\n\n### How to Reproduce?\n\n - Use Quarkus main + #29342\r\n - pick an app, use 999-SNAPSHOT, configure `quarkus.http.host=0.0.0.0`\r\n - open DevUI on another machine, point the browser to the instance running on the first machine\r\n - update anything under `/q/dev/io.quarkus.quarkus-vertx-http/config`\n\n### Output of `uname -a` or `ver`\n\n_No response_\n\n### Output of `java -version`\n\nJava 17\n\n### GraalVM version (if different from Java)\n\n_No response_\n\n### Quarkus version or git rev\n\nQuarkus main + #29342\n\n### Build tool (ie. output of `mvnw --version` or `gradlew --version`)\n\n_No response_\n\n### Additional information\n\n_No response_",
